<p>I am noticing that when I rotate and drive simultaneously, the ratio increases to around 1.1-1.2. Have you observed this behavior or do I need to check my simulator?</p>
<p>I’m guessing this is because the simulator is not a perfect representation of the swerve but I wanted to double check</p>","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":24,"updated_at":"2024-07-05T03:02:27.936Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":643,"readers_count":642,"score":158.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":468257,"topic_slug":"has-anyone-successfully-implemented-orbits-odometry-skid-detection","display_username":"Teddy","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":60033,"username":"catrix","name":"sam liu","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/c/dbc845/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":62239,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"That one guy obsessed with programming"},"post_url":"/t/has-anyone-successfully-implemented-orbits-odometry-skid-detection/468257/5","custom_user_title":"That one guy obsessed with programming","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3411232,"name":"Saathvik","username":"brainiac","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/b/8797f3/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-07-25T19:45:55.932Z","cooked":"<p>This code mainly focuses on the differences between the modules if I’m not mistaken. You could also add another skidding ratio calculation based on a good reference skidding ratio based on calculations done with fresh tread. Then, by comparing the skidding ratios of the current and reference ratios, you can get the overall skidding ratio of the entire drivetrain relative to the least possible skidding.</p>","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"posts_count":24,"updated_at":"2024-07-25T19:45:55.932Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":6,"reads":528,"readers_count":527,"score":140.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":468257,"topic_slug":"has-anyone-successfully-implemented-orbits-odometry-skid-detection","display_username":"Saathvik","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":60033,"username":"catrix","name":"sam liu","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/c/dbc845/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":64187,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Programmer"},"post_url":"/t/has-anyone-successfully-implemented-orbits-odometry-skid-detection/468257/6","custom_user_title":"Programmer","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3411275,"name":"Teddy","username":"dragonblade316","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/dragonblade316/{size}/211424_2.png","created_at":"2024-07-25T23:08:32.278Z","cooked":"<p>The skidding ratio should never be much higher than 1 under normal operation. Any higher and you can assume the robot is skidding. From there you can figure out out much it is skidding (for example if one module skids and the ratio is 2, then you can assume that module is moving twice as fast as it should.</p>","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"posts_count":24,"updated_at":"2024-07-25T23:08:32.278Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":6,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":5,"reads":472,"readers_count":471,"score":119.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":468257,"topic_slug":"has-anyone-successfully-implemented-orbits-odometry-skid-detection","display_username":"Teddy","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":64187,"username":"brainiac","name":"Saathvik","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/b/8797f3/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":62239,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"That one guy obsessed with programming"},"post_url":"/t/has-anyone-successfully-implemented-orbits-odometry-skid-detection/468257/7","custom_user_title":"That one guy obsessed with programming","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3411348,"name":"sam liu","username":"catrix","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/c/dbc845/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-07-26T05:11:40.620Z","cooked":"<p>Well, I don’t really think skidding detection works really well in simulation.  Because the swerve module is considered to be two DCMotors for most swerve simulations, it does not simulate how the wheels interact with the floor.  The odometry will behave as if the robot is sitting on a cart and the wheels are spinning in mid-air.<br>
I suggest testing this function on a real robot, or you can check out <a href="https://github.com/Shenzhen-Robotics-Alliance/Maple-Swerve-Skeleton/blob/dev/src/main/java/frc/robot/utils/CompetitionFieldUtils/Simulation/SwerveDriveSimulation.java" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">Our Swerve Simulation Code</a> which actually simulates all the friction and dynamics.</p>","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"posts_count":24,"updated_at":"2024-07-26T05:11:40.620Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":430,"readers_count":429,"score":101.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":468257,"topic_slug":"has-anyone-successfully-implemented-orbits-odometry-skid-detection","display_username":"sam liu","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/Shenzhen-Robotics-Alliance/Maple-Swerve-Skeleton/blob/dev/src/main/java/frc/robot/utils/CompetitionFieldUtils/Simulation/SwerveDriveSimulation.java","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Maple-Swerve-Skeleton/src/main/java/frc/robot/utils/CompetitionFieldUtils/Simulation/SwerveDriveSimulation.java at dev · Shenzhen-Robotics-Alliance/Maple-Swerve-Skeleton · GitHub","clicks":23}],"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":62239,"username":"dragonblade316","name":"Teddy","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/dragonblade316/{size}/211424_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":60033,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"CE Student @ UWaterloo | 5516 Alum "},"post_url":"/t/has-anyone-successfully-implemented-orbits-odometry-skid-detection/468257/8","